title: Vintage Czech
content:
[http://www.flickr.com/photos/katanan/3934463174/in/photostream/](http://web.archive.org/web/20131014025114/http:/www.flickr.com/photos/katanan/3934463174/in/photostream/)  
Can you guys think of similar digital typefaces to "Doska-Franckovka"?  
Is this a familiar font?
author: johnnydib

comments.content:
I'll go with Dispatch by Cyrus Highsmith!

[http://www.fontbureau.com/fonts/Dispatch](http://web.archive.org/web/20131014025114/http:/www.fontbureau.com/fonts/Dispatch "http://www.fontbureau.com/fonts/Dispatch")

Very interesting. Thanks.  
I'm gonna assume the original is a custom Logotype unless someone says otherwise :D

Or perhaps [Tovarich](http://web.archive.org/web/20131014025114/http:/dezcom.com/), from Typophile's own Chris Lozos. You could try e-mailing him through the contact link on [his Typophile user page](http://web.archive.org/web/20131014025114/http:/typophile.com/user/3135) if you're interested in it.
